metadata.name: fx_dungeon_2 #23
metadata.description:
Welcome to fx_dungeon_2, a little roguelike experiment living on the Tezos blockchain. Will you be able to get out of it alive? Each token features a randomly generated dungeon with limited resources. The layout is the same every time (on the same token), but you'll need to master each level perfectly if you want to beat the game - it's very difficult! And if you die, you need to start over ;) To beat the game, you need to go up in the dungeon until you find the final upward stairs!

A warning: this thing is not optimized for mobile phones. You'll need computer to play it! Additionally, while I did my best to bugfix and playtest with friends and helpful members of the community, there might still be bugs that I will be able to fix only in future iterations of the game.

## Controls
[W,A,S,D] or [↑ ↓ → ←] to move
[SPACE] or [E] to interact with stairs you are on or doors you are facing
[I] to bring up / exit the character screen
[P] to toggle sound
[R] to restart the game

## Characters
- The game features different character classes, with different strength, resistance and hunger stats
- The stronger a character is, the more damage it will do to creatures around the dungeon
- The more resistant a character is, the less damage it will receive from enemies and structures

### Warriors
- Warriors have average strength and defense stats. They have an average attack speed

### Berserkers
- Berserks are less strong but more resistant than warriors. They are slow to attack

### Assassins
- Assassins are very strong, but are not very resistant and they take damage very easily. They have a superior attack speed

## Exploration
- There are different floors to explore, from 2 (very common) up to 7 (very rare)
- On each floor you'll find obstacles to break, potions and enemies to fight
- Will you manage your resources correctly? If you die, you'll need to restart the game!
- The map will reveal itself as you explore it

## Potions

## Combat
- To attack an enemy, you must need to be in a tile next to it
- To attack an enemy, just press the key to move towards it
- Combat happens in real time. Smash that keyboard!

### Enemies
- There are different types of enemies, some are weaker and some are stronger
- Rats are very fast, but also very weak and easily killed. They are the most common in the dungeon
- Skeletons are slow, but they do more damage than a rat. They are also less common
- Imps are fast and strong enemies with high defense stats. If you spot one, prepare to smash that keyboard to kill it! They are a rare type of enemy
- There's no UI indications of the current enemy status, approach new fights carefully! You'll know when an enemy is dead when, well, it's dead
- Enemies might look the same, but some are stronger and some are weaker than others, while maintaining their general feel

## Console conditions
- You just got this game out of a yard sale, you can't expect it to be in perfect conditions, but it can happen!
- Despite the conditions of the game console, rest assured that the game will run with no bugs (unless myself, poor coder as I am, messed up with some bits of the code)!

metadata.name: ARAUCO #76
metadata.description:
The Araucaria Araucana, also known as pewén, is a sacred tree for the Mapuche and an emblem of Chile. With an origin dating back 260 million years to the Triassic period, it is part of the oldest forests on the planet. These ancient trees are endangered due to logging, forest fires, and grazing.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the Wünelfe star, and the staggered cross Ngümin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest. 

–

Press 's' to export a 4960x7016 PNG file suitable for A2 printing at 300 dpi.

Made with p5js.

Patricio Isaías, September 2022

metadata.name: glory hole$ #424
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: Cloverfield #24
metadata.description:
"Nature is the source of all true knowledge".

Have you ever taken the time to look, deeply look, at all the details in a humble patch of grass ?

In this tiny microcosm, a constant, fierce battle is going on, day after day, plants reaching out for sun, down for access to soil, fighting for survival. Smaller grasses form groups, alliances making it harder for taller ones to take over. Dead leaves remind us that some of them lost the fight, fallen warriors who, soon enough, will be forgotten too. Growth, decay, life, death, the endless cycle, right in front of our eyes.

It is fascinating, and, for me at least, an endless source of inspiration.

It is my hope that, through this project, you will take the time to take a closer look at nature, and that, as the pale blue dot we call home keeps getting drier and drier, remember that even humble patches of grass should not be taken for granted.


Key commands:
's' - save as png
'b' - make the background transparent (for printing)
'1', '2, '4' - set the pixel density, for resolutions up to 8000x8000

This updated version of the project should render on mobile devices, albeit with slightly reduced quality. 
If you want to save the image for printing, I recommend you do so on desktop.

metadata.name: Освобождение #19
metadata.description:
Освобождение (Eng.: Release) is the 3rd part of the current series of my Suprematism, textures and colours study.
This work shows the process of colours leaving their constraining shapes, trying to occupy more area. 

——————

Rendering takes around 30-40 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [Arrow Up / Down] to increase / decrease the drawing speed.
Press [1…6] to change the image resolution up to 10k.
Press [C] after the image is rendered to see 2 different states.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Sep. 2022.

metadata.name: Forgotten Memories #65
metadata.description:
Memories can be dark or they can be bright. Sometimes they are faint and pale, sometimes they are vivid and colorful. Sometimes they are hard to forget, sometimes they are easy to remember.

Memories are easily interrupted or even fractured, but they are also mostly always connected with other memories, whether they are related or not.

Forgotten Memories is what I consider to be my most ambitious study of color harmony yet. Each color represents a different category of memory, which are stored in our mind in layers of time. Their shapes differ in width and length depending on how weak/strong the memory was and how long it lasted.

Once a memory is forgotten, it may or may never be remembered again. But one thing that is not to be forgotten is that whether we choose to forget or remember, we are made of our memories.

* * *

Press S to save as PNG.
Press 1 to save with 1000px height.
Press 2 to save with 2000px height.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
License: LICENSE.txt
